article.description: Michael Littlejohn posted 17 points as Tennessee State topped Cal Poly 82-72 in the Las Vegas Invitational on Thursday.
article.headline: Littlejohn lifts Tennessee State over Cal Poly 82-72
article.linkText: Littlejohn lifts Tennessee State over Cal Poly 82-72
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Michael Littlejohn posted 17 points as Tennessee State topped Cal Poly 82-72 in the Las Vegas Invitational on Thursday. Mark Freeman had 16 points for Tennessee State (4-3). Jon Brown added 10 points and nine rebounds, and Jy'lan Washington had 10 points. The Tigers shot 48.2% from the field, including 11 of 19 3-pointers. Littlejohn scored 14 of his points in the first half and Freeman added 11 as TSU led 44-31. Junior Ballard had 19 points for the Mustangs (1-6), who have lost four games in a row. Colby Rogers added 14 points, and Tuukka Jaakkola had 12 points. Cal Poly was outrebounded 35-23. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
